01:03:37,847 --> 01:03:40,981
The data you copied has
military-grade encryption.

754
01:03:42,284 --> 01:03:44,518
You know, I bet with that dress,

755
01:03:44,520 --> 01:03:47,454
9 out of 10 men will let you
get away with anything.

756
01:03:47,456 --> 01:03:48,956
But you're the 10th?

757
01:03:48,958 --> 01:03:51,358
I'm guessing I'm the first

758
01:03:51,360 --> 01:03:53,727
to see through that babe-in-the-woods act.

759
01:03:54,796 --> 01:03:56,463
You don't know me,

760
01:03:56,465 --> 01:03:58,265
but I've known a few women like you.

761
01:04:01,603 --> 01:04:04,538
Oh, I don't think you've ever
known a woman like me.

762
01:04:06,208 --> 01:04:09,310
You know, it's true what
they say about little boys.

763
01:04:09,312 --> 01:04:12,079
Born with no natural inclination to share.

764
01:04:13,281 --> 01:04:15,516
I didn't steal your drive.

765
01:04:15,518 --> 01:04:17,785
I borrowed it.

766
01:04:17,787 --> 01:04:20,754
You'll find it in the glove
compartment of your car.

767
01:04:21,990 --> 01:04:23,090
Mr. Wayne.

768
01:06:16,338 --> 01:06:17,471
Did you get it?

769
01:06:17,473 --> 01:06:18,806
The rock?

770
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:20,140
Yeah, we got it.

771
01:06:45,934 --> 01:06:47,034
I'm sorry.

772
01:06:48,704 --> 01:06:51,705
Get down! Get down now!

773
01:07:07,522 --> 01:07:08,622
No!

774
01:09:02,804 --> 01:09:04,505
She was my world.

775
01:09:06,141 --> 01:09:08,041
And you took her from me.

776
01:09:18,487 --> 01:09:20,521
<i>Bruce!</i>

777
01:09:20,523 --> 01:09:23,590
Bruce! Listen to me now!

778
01:09:26,861 --> 01:09:28,996
It's Lois!

779
01:09:28,998 --> 01:09:30,931
It's Lois Lane!

780
01:09:31,633 --> 01:09:33,200
<i>She's the key!</i>

781
01:09:35,003 --> 01:09:37,604
Am I too soon?

782
01:09:39,008 --> 01:09:41,508
I'm too soon!

783
01:09:41,510 --> 01:09:43,844
<i>You're right about him!</i>

784
01:09:43,846 --> 01:09:46,680
<i>You've always been right about him!</i>

785
01:09:46,682 --> 01:09:49,049
Fear him! Fear him!

786
01:09:49,851 --> 01:09:50,951
Find us, Bruce!

787
01:09:52,020 --> 01:09:53,620
<i>You have to find us!</i>

788
01:10:57,919 --> 01:11:00,020
<i>The</i> white Portuguese <i>is not a man.</i>

789
01:11:00,022 --> 01:11:01,121
<i>It's a ship.</i>

790
01:11:03,791 --> 01:11:07,027
Master Wayne, since the age of seven

791
01:11:07,029 --> 01:11:09,096
you have been to the art of deception

792
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:11,698
as Mozart to the harpsichord.

793
01:11:11,700 --> 01:11:15,469
But you've never been
too hot at lying to me.

794
01:11:17,405 --> 01:11:20,374
The <i>white Portuguese</i> is not
carrying a dirty bomb.

795
01:11:20,376 --> 01:11:22,009
<i>What is it carrying?</i>

796
01:11:23,244 --> 01:11:24,544
It's a weapon.

797
01:11:25,380 --> 01:11:27,114
It's a rock.

798
01:11:27,116 --> 01:11:30,717
A mineral capable of weakening
Kryptonian cells.

799
01:11:30,719 --> 01:11:32,452
<i>The first sample big enough
to mean something</i>

800
01:11:32,454 --> 01:11:34,488
turned up in the Indian ocean
three months ago.

801
01:11:34,490 --> 01:11:36,456
It is now aboard the <i>white Portuguese</i>

802
01:11:36,458 --> 01:11:38,959
being delivered to Lex Luthor.

803
01:11:38,961 --> 01:11:40,994
Who I am going to steal it from.

804
01:11:40,996 --> 01:11:42,929
To keep it out of Luthor's hands.

805
01:11:42,931 --> 01:11:44,197
To destroy it.

806
01:11:45,633 --> 01:11:46,700
No.

807
01:11:49,470 --> 01:11:51,905
You're gonna go to war?

808
01:11:51,907 --> 01:11:57,911
That son of a bitch brought
the war to us two years ago.

809
01:11:57,913 --> 01:12:01,515
Jesus, Alfred. Count the dead.
Thousands of people.

810
01:12:02,784 --> 01:12:05,619
What's next? Millions?

811
01:12:05,621 --> 01:12:08,288
He has the power to wipe out
the entire human race,

812
01:12:08,290 --> 01:12:10,857
and if we believe there's even a
1% chance that he is our enemy,

813
01:12:10,859 --> 01:12:14,027
we have to take it
as an absolute certainty.

814
01:12:14,029 --> 01:12:15,429
And we have to destroy him.

815
01:12:15,431 --> 01:12:18,098
But he is not our enemy.

816
01:12:18,933 --> 01:12:20,967
Not today.

817
01:12:20,969 --> 01:12:23,670
20 years in Gotham, Alfred.

818
01:12:23,672 --> 01:12:25,605
We've seen what promises are worth.

819
01:12:26,808 --> 01:12:28,442
How many good guys are left.

820
01:12:29,844 --> 01:12:31,511
How many stayed that way.

821
01:12:34,449 --> 01:12:35,949
14 hours.

822
01:12:38,519 --> 01:12:41,054
My name is Clark Kent.
I'm from the <i>Daily Planet.</i>

823
01:12:44,692 --> 01:12:49,029
I'm trying to find out what
happened to an inmate, a Santos.

824
01:12:49,031 --> 01:12:50,731
I can't give out that information.

825
01:13:08,216 --> 01:13:09,549
Mommy!

826
01:13:13,488 --> 01:13:15,889
Mrs. Santos?

827
01:13:15,891 --> 01:13:18,358
<i>May I ask you a few questions?</i>

828
01:13:18,360 --> 01:13:20,160
He wasn't my husband.

829
01:13:20,162 --> 01:13:21,561
But I know what he did.

830
01:13:22,697 --> 01:13:24,865
But he was a father.

831
01:13:24,867 --> 01:13:26,833
He was that, too.

832
01:13:26,835 --> 01:13:28,435
They took him out of Gotham Central.

833
01:13:28,437 --> 01:13:30,670
They moved him to Metropolis.

834
01:13:30,672 --> 01:13:32,572
But inside they know.

835
01:13:32,574 --> 01:13:35,075
They know the mark all over.
Guards don't care.

836
01:13:35,077 --> 01:13:36,476
Bat's the judge.

837
01:13:37,545 --> 01:13:39,246
One man decides who lives.

838
01:13:39,248 --> 01:13:41,748
How is that justice?
Talk to me.

839
01:13:41,750 --> 01:13:44,785
Help me change it.
With what? Your pen?

840
01:13:44,787 --> 01:13:47,721
A man like that, words don't stop him.

841
01:13:47,723 --> 01:13:49,189
You know stops him?

842
01:13:49,857 --> 01:13:51,124
A fist.

843
01:13:55,096 --> 01:13:56,496
<i>Kent, I want to talk to you.</i>

844
01:13:58,900 --> 01:14:00,434
Kent!

845
01:14:00,436 --> 01:14:02,602
Where does he go?
Where does he go, Jenny?

846
01:14:02,604 --> 01:14:04,604
I don't...
I don't know.

847
01:14:04,606 --> 01:14:05,806
Clicks his heels three times,

848
01:14:05,808 --> 01:14:07,507
goes back to Kansas, I suppose.

849
01:14:09,410 --> 01:14:10,577
Son of a...

850
01:14:22,590 --> 01:14:23,824
<i>Turn it!</i>

851
01:14:23,826 --> 01:14:25,358
<i>Turn it!</i>

852
01:15:08,803 --> 01:15:10,237
Move out!

853
01:15:46,073 --> 01:15:47,307
Go, go, go, go!

854
01:16:26,347 --> 01:16:27,414
No!

855
01:17:52,466 --> 01:17:53,867
Where is he?

856
01:19:13,748 --> 01:19:16,449
Next time they shine
your light in the sky,

857
01:19:16,451 --> 01:19:18,284
don't go to it.

858
01:19:18,286 --> 01:19:20,687
The Bat is dead. Bury it.

859
01:19:22,289 --> 01:19:23,590
Consider this mercy.

860
01:19:25,793 --> 01:19:27,193
<i>Tell me.</i>

861
01:19:31,599 --> 01:19:33,133
<i>Do you bleed?</i>

862
01:19:41,776 --> 01:19:43,109
<i>You will.</i>

863
01:21:25,379 --> 01:21:28,214
I don't have a halo over me,
Mr. Secretary.

864
01:21:28,216 --> 01:21:30,250
I went into the desert, people died.

865
01:21:30,252 --> 01:21:32,385
It keeps me awake.
It should.

866
01:21:38,192 --> 01:21:39,893
If you think that Superman is a murderer,

867
01:21:39,895 --> 01:21:41,895
then throw it away.

868
01:21:41,897 --> 01:21:43,796
But I don't believe you think that.

869
01:21:46,867 --> 01:21:49,903
<i>How do we determine what's good?</i>

870
01:21:49,905 --> 01:21:52,739
In a democracy, good is a conversation,

871
01:21:52,741 --> 01:21:55,608
<i>not a unilateral decision.</i>

872
01:21:55,610 --> 01:21:58,278
So I urge Superman to come

873
01:21:58,280 --> 01:22:00,079
<i>to this hill of the people tomorrow</i>

874
01:22:00,081 --> 01:22:02,782
<i>to see those who have suffered.</i>

875
01:22:02,784 --> 01:22:06,052
<i>The world needs to know
what happened in that desert.</i>

876
01:22:06,054 --> 01:22:08,554
<i>And to know what he stands for.</i>

877
01:22:08,556 --> 01:22:10,757
<i>How far will he take his power?</i>

878
01:22:12,293 --> 01:22:16,162
<i>Does he act by our will or by his own?</i>

879
01:22:23,938 --> 01:22:26,839
<i>People hate what they don't understand.</i>

880
01:22:28,442 --> 01:22:32,111
But they see what you do,
and they know who you are.

881
01:22:33,614 --> 01:22:36,950
You're not a killer, a threat.

882
01:22:38,385 --> 01:22:40,687
I never wanted this world to have you.

883
01:22:44,125 --> 01:22:47,493
Be their hero, Clark.
Be their monument.

884
01:22:47,495 --> 01:22:49,495
Be their angel.

885
01:22:49,497 --> 01:22:51,364
Be anything they need you to be.

886
01:22:52,099 --> 01:22:53,800
Or be none of it.

887
01:22:55,769 --> 01:22:57,804
You don't owe this world a thing.

888
01:22:58,973 --> 01:23:00,640
You never did.

889
01:23:03,077 --> 01:23:06,346
<i>This is Deniros.
Transfer available to Kane Avenue.</i>

890
01:23:06,348 --> 01:23:07,814
<i>Please, mind your step.</i>

891
01:23:37,811 --> 01:23:40,113
<i>I have to speak to the Senator today.</i>

892
01:23:40,115 --> 01:23:41,681
<i>You cannot see the Senator today.</i>

893
01:23:41,683 --> 01:23:43,182
<i>I need to speak to her before the hearing.</i>

894
01:23:43,184 --> 01:23:45,118
<i>Do you understand how important this is?</i>

895
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:46,652
<i>I cannot let you see the Senator.</i>

896
01:23:46,654 --> 01:23:48,454
<i>Please, I need to speak to her.</i>

897
01:23:48,456 --> 01:23:51,357
<i>Please, Madam. I beg of you!
Please don't do this!</i>

898
01:23:51,359 --> 01:23:52,859
<i>This is so important!</i>

899
01:23:52,861 --> 01:23:55,395
<i>Come with me.
Don't touch me!</i>

900
01:23:55,397 --> 01:23:57,597
Please! I'm sorry.
She wouldn't leave.

901
01:23:59,366 --> 01:24:02,168
I didn't tell you the truth.

902
01:24:02,170 --> 01:24:05,071
C.I. Thinks
the desert was a setup.

903
01:24:05,073 --> 01:24:07,240
Somebody wanted Superman to look guilty.

904
01:24:08,042 --> 01:24:10,043
The bullet?

905
01:24:18,419 --> 01:24:19,886
The metal was developed
by a private company.

906
01:24:19,888 --> 01:24:21,187
What company?

907
01:24:21,189 --> 01:24:22,789
LexCorp.

908
01:24:23,891 --> 01:24:25,725
Lex Luthor?

909
01:24:25,727 --> 01:24:28,877
He also had private security
contractors at the desert compound.

910
01:24:32,533 --> 01:24:34,033
Go on record.

911
01:24:34,035 --> 01:24:37,737
Not a chance.
It's classified.

912
01:24:37,739 --> 01:24:38,938
I happen to like my job.

913
01:24:38,940 --> 01:24:40,706
It doesn't make sense.

914
01:24:40,708 --> 01:24:42,775
You said that the ambush was
arranged to frame Superman,

915
01:24:42,777 --> 01:24:45,277
but how could they know
that he'd show up in the...

916
01:24:51,718 --> 01:24:53,953
In the middle of the desert.
Thank you.

917
01:24:57,258 --> 01:25:00,860
The Senate hearing is expected
to get underway any minute now.

918
01:25:00,862 --> 01:25:03,096
And of course the big
unknown in all of this is

919
01:25:03,098 --> 01:25:04,597
will Superman show up?

920
01:25:04,599 --> 01:25:05,598
That is what they're really
waiting to see.

921
01:25:05,600 --> 01:25:06,899
Mr. Keefe. Mr. Keefe.

922
01:25:06,901 --> 01:25:08,434
Soledad o'Brien, <i>in the Moment.</i>

923
01:25:08,436 --> 01:25:09,936
Quick question for you.

924
01:25:09,938 --> 01:25:11,304
You're heading in
to meet with the Senators.

925
01:25:11,306 --> 01:25:13,106
What will you tell them?

926
01:25:13,108 --> 01:25:16,042
<i>I've come here to tell them to wake up.</i>

927
01:25:16,044 --> 01:25:18,211
<i>This is flesh and blood.</i>

928
01:25:18,213 --> 01:25:19,645
<i>He has delivered a war here.</i>

929
01:25:19,647 --> 01:25:21,881
<i>And this...</i>

930
01:25:21,883 --> 01:25:23,249
<i>This is what war looks like.</i>

931
01:25:23,251 --> 01:25:25,418
<i>I have nothing.</i>

932
01:25:25,420 --> 01:25:27,787
<i>There are plenty of people, sir,
who would say he's their hero.</i>

933
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:29,455
<i>He is not a hero.</i>

934
01:25:29,457 --> 01:25:32,458
Grace, can you get Greg up here, please?

935
01:25:32,460 --> 01:25:34,660
Right now.

936
01:25:34,662 --> 01:25:36,729
An anonymous source can verify everything

937
01:25:36,731 --> 01:25:38,464
I told you about what happened in Nairomi.

938
01:25:38,466 --> 01:25:41,100
An anonymous source?
<i>Run it.</i>

939
01:25:41,102 --> 01:25:43,236
Luthor engineered the desert.

940
01:25:43,238 --> 01:25:45,404
It was an ambush for Superman.

941
01:25:45,406 --> 01:25:46,973
Trust your reporter.
Think Watergate.

942
01:25:46,975 --> 01:25:49,108
<i>Yeah, and you need to think litigate.</i>

943
01:25:49,110 --> 01:25:51,644
<i>If you're wrong, Luthor will sue
the paper out of existence.</i>

944
01:25:51,646 --> 01:25:52,812
<i>You need proof.</i>

945
01:25:52,814 --> 01:25:54,347
No. It needs to run now.

946
01:25:54,349 --> 01:25:56,015
<i>Before the hearing.</i>

947
01:25:56,017 --> 01:25:57,517
<i>If Superman knows,
it might change what he says.</i>

948
01:25:57,519 --> 01:25:59,785
I am not going to risk the paper

949
01:25:59,787 --> 01:26:01,487
so that you can pass notes in class

950
01:26:01,489 --> 01:26:02,755
to the man that rescued you.

951
01:26:02,757 --> 01:26:04,323
McGraw: <i>He paid her?</i>

952
01:26:04,325 --> 01:26:07,126
Not only paid her.
He threatened her.

953
01:26:07,128 --> 01:26:09,529
Gave her a script to learn.

954
01:26:09,531 --> 01:26:12,298
Her parents are alive back home.

955
01:26:12,300 --> 01:26:14,300
But the girl's got a conscience.

956
01:26:14,302 --> 01:26:17,302
He's been using the committee
as his puppet theater. Senator!

957
01:26:17,938 --> 01:26:19,338
Hi, you.

958
01:26:19,340 --> 01:26:20,706
Don't go anywhere.
I want to talk to you.

959
01:26:20,708 --> 01:26:22,708
Uh, you know what?
Mercy, you go in

960
01:26:22,710 --> 01:26:24,877
and make sure no one takes my seat.

961
01:26:24,879 --> 01:26:26,145
So what you been up to?

962
01:26:26,147 --> 01:26:27,947
I'm just here to tell my story.

963
01:26:27,949 --> 01:26:29,482
That I was willing to finance
a Kryptonian deterrent,

964
01:26:29,484 --> 01:26:31,150
but a certain junior Senator from Kentucky

965
01:26:31,152 --> 01:26:33,219
decided to block it.

966
01:26:33,221 --> 01:26:36,856
Yes, the chair of the committee
on Superman is soft on security.

967
01:26:36,858 --> 01:26:39,525
Greg, why hasn't he been getting
our checks? He is, Mr. Wayne.

968
01:26:39,527 --> 01:26:42,195
He gets a check from
the victims fund every month.

969
01:26:42,197 --> 01:26:44,697
He returns them.

970
01:26:44,699 --> 01:26:46,232
<i>...who lost both his legs</i>

971
01:26:46,234 --> 01:26:48,701
<i>in those horrific events in Metropolis</i>

972
01:26:48,703 --> 01:26:50,403
<i>that happened two years ago.</i>

973
01:26:50,405 --> 01:26:51,604
Jesus.

974
01:26:53,674 --> 01:26:55,341
Why haven't I seen this?

975
01:26:55,343 --> 01:26:57,376
<i>I'm sorry.
I'll get to the bottom of it.</i>

976
01:26:57,378 --> 01:27:00,079
<i>And there he is.
Superman is here.</i>

977
01:27:00,081 --> 01:27:02,348
<i>He is actually
at the United States Capitol.</i>

978
01:27:02,350 --> 01:27:04,483
<i>This is really a historic moment.</i>

979
01:27:04,485 --> 01:27:06,819
<i>Now we expect that Superman will give</i>

980
01:27:06,821 --> 01:27:08,888
<i>some kind of a statement to the Senate,</i>

981
01:27:08,890 --> 01:27:11,624
<i>to the American people,
and, of course, to the world.</i>

982
01:27:12,392 --> 01:27:13,893
He's here. He came.

983
01:27:13,895 --> 01:27:16,395
He's above the Capitol.
Ah.

984
01:27:16,397 --> 01:27:19,065
You are gonna be on the
hot seat in there, Junebug.

985
01:27:19,067 --> 01:27:20,733
I grew up on a farm.

986
01:27:20,735 --> 01:27:23,202
I know how to wrestle a pig.

987
01:27:23,204 --> 01:27:25,504
Do you know the oldest lie
in America, Senator?

988
01:27:26,440 --> 01:27:28,307
It's that power can be innocent.

989
01:27:30,410 --> 01:27:31,644
Good luck.

990
01:28:07,547 --> 01:28:09,715
Oh, Miss...

991
01:28:09,717 --> 01:28:11,517
Rudy, she's good to go.

992
01:28:19,960 --> 01:28:21,060
Get out!

993
01:28:24,331 --> 01:28:27,166
Get out! Get out!
Superman! Superman!

994
01:28:34,274 --> 01:28:36,375
Another one came
this morning, Mr. Wayne.

995
01:29:15,549 --> 01:29:18,484
Let me say at the outset that
I'm grateful to our witness

996
01:29:18,486 --> 01:29:21,354
for coming before us today.

997
01:29:21,356 --> 01:29:24,123
This is how a democracy works.

998
01:29:24,125 --> 01:29:26,859
We talk to each other.

999
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:32,365
We act by the consent
of the governed, sir.

1000
01:29:32,367 --> 01:29:35,701
<i>I have sat here before to say
that shadow interventions</i>

1001
01:29:35,703 --> 01:29:38,704
<i>will not be tolerated by this committee.</i>

1002
01:29:38,706 --> 01:29:40,239
<i>Neither will lies.</i>

1003
01:29:41,875 --> 01:29:45,311
Because today is a day for truth.

