01:55:45,204 --> 01:55:47,972
Hmm, yes, I do. I think
you will fight-fight-fight

1247
01:55:47,974 --> 01:55:49,941
for that special lady in your life.

1248
01:55:49,943 --> 01:55:52,243
She's safe on the ground.
How about you?

1249
01:55:52,245 --> 01:55:55,880
Close, but I am not talking about Lois.

1250
01:55:55,882 --> 01:56:00,284
No. Every boy's special lady
is his mother.

1251
01:56:05,958 --> 01:56:08,459
Martha, Martha, Martha.

1252
01:56:08,961 --> 01:56:10,428
Hmm.

1253
01:56:10,430 --> 01:56:14,398
Why, the mother of a flying
demon must be a witch.

1254
01:56:14,400 --> 01:56:17,268
The punishment for witches, what is that?

1255
01:56:17,270 --> 01:56:19,403
That's right.
Death by fire.

1256
01:56:21,440 --> 01:56:23,007
Mmm.

1257
01:56:28,981 --> 01:56:31,015
Where is she?

1258
01:56:31,017 --> 01:56:32,817
I don't know!
I would not let them tell me!

1259
01:56:32,819 --> 01:56:35,319
Uh-uh-uh!
If you kill me, Martha dies.

1260
01:56:35,321 --> 01:56:37,488
And if you fly away, mmm,
Martha also dies.

1261
01:56:37,490 --> 01:56:40,491
But if you kill the bat...

1262
01:56:40,493 --> 01:56:41,926
Martha lives.

1263
01:56:46,832 --> 01:56:50,101
There we go.
There we go. Hmm.

1264
01:56:52,671 --> 01:56:56,607
And now God bends to my will.

1265
01:57:02,280 --> 01:57:05,182
Ooh, now the cameras
are waiting at your ship.

1266
01:57:05,184 --> 01:57:07,451
For the world to see
the holes in the Holy.

1267
01:57:07,453 --> 01:57:08,953
Yes, the almighty comes clean

1268
01:57:08,955 --> 01:57:10,321
about how dirty he is when it counts.

1269
01:57:10,323 --> 01:57:12,023
To save Martha,

1270
01:57:12,025 --> 01:57:13,691
bring me the head of the Bat.

1271
01:57:17,195 --> 01:57:18,496
Ah.

1272
01:57:18,498 --> 01:57:21,365
Mother of God, would you look at the time?

1273
01:57:21,367 --> 01:57:23,701
When you came here, you had an hour.

1274
01:57:24,970 --> 01:57:26,871
Now it's less.

1275
01:58:28,533 --> 01:58:30,234
<i>Brooke Baldwin is on the scene.</i>

1276
01:58:30,236 --> 01:58:32,470
<i>Brooke, you're live on the air.
What are you seeing?</i>

1277
01:58:32,472 --> 01:58:34,472
There's something happening at the ship.

1278
01:58:35,440 --> 01:58:38,242
It's sending massive power surges.

1279
01:58:38,244 --> 01:58:40,077
<i>Police helicopters surrounding the area.</i>

1280
01:58:40,079 --> 01:58:42,813
<i>They've created a barricade
around this containment center.</i>

1281
01:58:42,815 --> 01:58:44,415
<i>And we're trying to get
a little bit closer here</i>

1282
01:58:44,417 --> 01:58:46,117
<i>to find out what's going on.</i>

1283
01:58:46,119 --> 01:58:48,119
<i>It is absolute chaos.
You can see that lightning,</i>

1284
01:58:48,121 --> 01:58:49,787
<i>those surges of electricity.</i>

1285
01:58:49,789 --> 01:58:53,057
<i>They seem to be getting
stronger by the minute.</i>

1286
01:58:53,059 --> 01:58:55,793
<i>Daily Planet.</i>

1287
01:58:55,795 --> 01:59:00,164
Lois. I have to go to Gotham
to convince him to help me.

1288
01:59:00,166 --> 01:59:01,232
Who?

1289
01:59:03,602 --> 01:59:05,636
Or he has to die.

1290
01:59:05,638 --> 01:59:06,871
Clark.

1291
01:59:10,242 --> 01:59:12,409
No one stays good in this world.

1292
01:59:21,353 --> 01:59:25,356
<i>But as of right now, much of the
city remains in the dark tonight.</i>

1293
01:59:25,358 --> 01:59:29,693
<i>Much chaos. Much confusing happening
on the streets of Metropolis tonight.</i>

1294
01:59:29,695 --> 01:59:31,862
<i>Those helicopters are still
surrounding the area.</i>

1295
01:59:31,864 --> 01:59:34,864
<i>I don't know if you can still
see those bolts of lightning...</i>

1296
02:01:36,254 --> 02:01:41,292
<i>2400 hours and 2 minutes.
Subject declining rapidly.</i>

1297
02:01:41,294 --> 02:01:43,360
<i>All procedural interventions have failed.</i>

1298
02:01:44,229 --> 02:01:45,796
<i>Outcome</i>

1299
02:01:48,400 --> 02:01:49,667
<i>will be death.</i>

1300
02:01:58,343 --> 02:02:01,145
<i>Dr. Silas stone suspending
all clinical protocol.</i>

1301
02:02:01,147 --> 02:02:07,885
<i>US gov, object 6-19-82
is successfully activated.</i>

1302
02:02:29,507 --> 02:02:30,808
<i>I need a chopper to Gotham.</i>

1303
02:02:30,810 --> 02:02:32,209
Call the heliport.

1304
02:02:32,211 --> 02:02:33,977
Chopper? We can
barely afford a bicycle.

1305
02:02:33,979 --> 02:02:35,145
You wanna chase a story?

1306
02:02:35,147 --> 02:02:36,447
Go to the ship.

1307
02:02:36,449 --> 02:02:37,815
Superman's probably there already.

1308
02:02:37,817 --> 02:02:40,584
Perry, it's not for a story.

1309
02:02:45,457 --> 02:02:47,157
Jenny, get her a chopper to Gotham.

1310
02:02:47,159 --> 02:02:49,693
And forget the heliport.
Put it on the Goddamn roof.

1311
02:02:49,695 --> 02:02:51,195
On the roof, Lois!

1312
02:02:53,865 --> 02:02:55,532
Where are we headed?

1313
02:02:55,534 --> 02:02:56,734
There!

1314
02:03:12,717 --> 02:03:15,753
<i>Well, here I am.</i>

1315
02:03:17,088 --> 02:03:18,455
Bruce. Please.

1316
02:03:20,225 --> 02:03:23,093
I was wrong.
You have to listen to me.

1317
02:03:23,095 --> 02:03:24,328
Lex wants us to...

1318
02:03:39,744 --> 02:03:42,079
You don't understand.

1319
02:03:42,081 --> 02:03:43,447
There's no time!

1320
02:03:45,083 --> 02:03:46,250
<i>I understand.</i>

1321
02:05:02,760 --> 02:05:04,328
Stay down!

1322
02:05:04,330 --> 02:05:06,763
If I wanted it, you'd be dead already.

1323
02:05:44,836 --> 02:05:46,136
<i>Breathe it in.</i>

1324
02:05:48,907 --> 02:05:50,774
<i>That's fear.</i>

1325
02:05:53,678 --> 02:05:55,112
<i>You're not brave.</i>

1326
02:05:59,417 --> 02:06:00,951
<i>Men are brave.</i>

1327
02:09:50,715 --> 02:09:55,385
<i>I bet your parents taught you
that you mean something.</i>

1328
02:09:55,387 --> 02:09:57,053
<i>That you're here for a reason.</i>

1329
02:09:58,556 --> 02:10:02,259
<i>My parents taught me a different lesson,</i>

1330
02:10:02,261 --> 02:10:04,728
<i>dying in the gutter</i>

1331
02:10:04,730 --> 02:10:06,730
<i>for no reason at all.</i>

1332
02:10:23,481 --> 02:10:26,149
<i>They taught me the world only makes sense</i>

1333
02:10:26,151 --> 02:10:28,218
<i>if you force it to.</i>

1334
02:11:06,557 --> 02:11:08,458
<i>You were never a God.</i>

1335
02:11:11,229 --> 02:11:13,396
<i>You were never even a man.</i>

1336
02:11:20,338 --> 02:11:23,707
You're letting him kill Martha.

1337
02:11:29,347 --> 02:11:31,147
<i>What does that mean?</i>

1338
02:11:32,350 --> 02:11:33,917
<i>Why did you say that name?</i>

1339
02:11:35,186 --> 02:11:37,754
Find him.

1340
02:11:38,990 --> 02:11:40,690
Save.

1341
02:11:40,692 --> 02:11:42,392
<i>Martha.</i>

1342
02:11:45,329 --> 02:11:46,730
<i>Martha.</i>

1343
02:12:17,528 --> 02:12:19,429
Martha.

1344
02:12:23,634 --> 02:12:24,934
<i>Why did you say that name?</i>

1345
02:12:26,738 --> 02:12:28,571
<i>Martha!
Why did you say that name?</i>

1346
02:12:28,573 --> 02:12:29,873
Clark! Stop!

1347
02:12:29,875 --> 02:12:31,241
Please! Stop!

1348
02:12:31,243 --> 02:12:32,909
<i>Why did you say that name?</i>

1349
02:12:32,911 --> 02:12:35,378
It's his mother's name!

1350
02:12:35,380 --> 02:12:37,647
It's his mother's name.

1351
02:13:09,247 --> 02:13:10,780
<i>We're not getting any answers.</i>

1352
02:13:10,782 --> 02:13:12,315
We're still right outside
the containment center.

1353
02:13:12,317 --> 02:13:13,516
A dangerous situation.

1354
02:13:13,518 --> 02:13:14,951
Military and police personnel

1355
02:13:14,953 --> 02:13:16,519
<i>surrounding the area.</i>

1356
02:13:32,036 --> 02:13:33,303
<i>Luthor.</i>

1357
02:13:33,305 --> 02:13:35,772
He wanted your life for hers.

1358
02:13:36,974 --> 02:13:38,808
She's losing time.

1359
02:13:38,810 --> 02:13:41,711
The scout ship seems to be
drawing power from the city.

1360
02:13:41,713 --> 02:13:43,279
It's got to be Lex.

1361
02:13:43,281 --> 02:13:46,016
<i>They need you at that ship.
I'll find her.</i>

1362
02:13:46,018 --> 02:13:48,118
My mother needs me.
<i>Wait.</i>

1363
02:13:49,220 --> 02:13:51,654
<i>I'll make you a promise.</i>

1364
02:13:51,656 --> 02:13:53,923
<i>Martha won't die tonight.</i>

1365
02:14:20,651 --> 02:14:22,018
<i>Master Wayne.</i>

1366
02:14:22,020 --> 02:14:23,253
<i>Alfred.</i>

1367
02:14:23,255 --> 02:14:25,021
Uh, I'm sorry for listening in,

1368
02:14:25,023 --> 02:14:26,556
but I've tracked the Russian's phone

1369
02:14:26,558 --> 02:14:28,224
to a warehouse near the port.

1370
02:14:28,226 --> 02:14:29,759
<i>You're locked onto it.</i>

1371
02:14:29,761 --> 02:14:31,327
<i>I don't deserve you, Alfred.</i>

1372
02:14:31,329 --> 02:14:33,797
No, sir. You don't.

1373
02:14:54,552 --> 02:14:56,486
I'm afraid this is goodbye.

1374
02:14:58,389 --> 02:15:02,592
And every time we say goodbye,
you die a little.

1375
02:15:15,739 --> 02:15:17,540
- Take it down.
- Go! Go!

1376
02:15:40,898 --> 02:15:42,298
<i>You have to take it, Alfred.</i>

1377
02:15:42,900 --> 02:15:44,801
Ah, right.

1378
02:15:44,803 --> 02:15:46,870
Commencing drone mode.

1379
02:15:49,840 --> 02:15:51,674
Thermal imaging is showing me

1380
02:15:51,676 --> 02:15:54,277
two dozen hostiles on the third floor.

1381
02:15:54,279 --> 02:15:56,679
Why don't I drop you off on the second?

1382
02:19:01,765 --> 02:19:03,499
Drop it.

1383
02:19:05,169 --> 02:19:07,070
I said drop it!

1384
02:19:08,038 --> 02:19:09,372
I'll kill her.

1385
02:19:11,208 --> 02:19:13,443
Believe me, I'll do it.

1386
02:19:16,313 --> 02:19:17,447
<i>I believe you.</i>

1387
02:19:29,828 --> 02:19:32,862
<i>It's okay.
I'm a friend of your son's.</i>

1388
02:19:32,864 --> 02:19:35,765
I figured.
The cape.

1389
02:20:03,862 --> 02:20:05,395
"Late, late," says the white rabbit.

1390
02:20:05,397 --> 02:20:07,196
<i>40 seconds to animation.</i>

1391
02:20:07,198 --> 02:20:08,831
Right, wabbit?

1392
02:20:08,833 --> 02:20:12,602
Hmm. Out of tricks,
out of time.

1393
02:20:13,670 --> 02:20:16,172
And one Bat head short.

1394
02:20:16,174 --> 02:20:18,007
<i>30 seconds to animation.</i>

1395
02:20:18,009 --> 02:20:19,776
Ah. That'll be the cook.

1396
02:20:19,778 --> 02:20:20,943
Excuse me.

1397
02:20:20,945 --> 02:20:23,880
Uh, Gotham roast.
Well done.

1398
02:20:23,882 --> 02:20:26,048
Hello. Break the bad news.

1399
02:20:26,050 --> 02:20:28,951
<i>I'd rather do the breaking in person.</i>

1400
02:20:28,953 --> 02:20:30,686
<i>20 seconds to animation.</i>

1401
02:20:30,688 --> 02:20:31,754
You've lost.

1402
02:20:32,723 --> 02:20:33,956
I don't know how to lose.

1403
02:20:33,958 --> 02:20:35,124
You'll learn.

1404
02:20:35,126 --> 02:20:36,759
I'll learn.

1405
02:20:36,761 --> 02:20:39,262
I don't hate the sinner.

1406
02:20:39,264 --> 02:20:41,364
- I hate the sin.
<i>- 10 seconds to animation.</i>

1407
02:20:41,366 --> 02:20:44,033
And yours, my friend, is existing.

1408
02:20:44,868 --> 02:20:46,469
I cannot let you win.

1409
02:20:46,471 --> 02:20:47,737
I gave the bat a fighting chance to do it,

1410
02:20:47,739 --> 02:20:48,805
but he was not strong enough.

1411
02:20:48,807 --> 02:20:50,807
So, if man won't kill God...

1412
02:20:50,809 --> 02:20:52,975
<i>...two, one.</i>

1413
02:20:54,645 --> 02:20:55,845
...the Devil will do it!

1414
02:21:12,464 --> 02:21:13,896
Perry!

1415
02:21:13,898 --> 02:21:16,566
All right.
Stay calm, everybody!

1416
02:21:16,568 --> 02:21:18,000
<i>We're getting reports
there are total blackouts</i>

1417
02:21:18,002 --> 02:21:20,770
<i>in the north and to
the northwest of the city.</i>

1418
02:21:20,772 --> 02:21:22,171
<i>Federal authorities
are trying to determine</i>

1419
02:21:22,173 --> 02:21:24,474
<i>if this is part of
a larger terrorist attack.</i>

1420
02:21:28,846 --> 02:21:31,948
Ancient Kryptonian deformity.

1421
02:21:31,950 --> 02:21:35,685
Hmm. Blood of my blood.

1422
02:21:42,192 --> 02:21:44,360
Born to destroy you.

1423
02:21:47,097 --> 02:21:49,165
Your Doomsday.

1424
02:22:12,289 --> 02:22:15,091
Now God is good

1425
02:22:15,626 --> 02:22:17,093
as dead.

1426
02:22:20,298 --> 02:22:21,597
Oh!

1427
02:23:40,711 --> 02:23:42,111
Potus joining.

1428
02:23:42,113 --> 02:23:43,479
Mr. President.

1429
02:23:43,481 --> 02:23:45,147
<i>What the hell is it, Calvin?</i>

1430
02:23:45,149 --> 02:23:46,816
<i>These are live images from the top</i>

1431
02:23:46,818 --> 02:23:49,051
<i>of the LexCorp tower
in downtown Metropolis.</i>

1432
02:23:49,053 --> 02:23:50,886
<i>Military aircraft are on the scene.</i>

1433
02:24:02,800 --> 02:24:04,767
Are you hurt, Ma'am?
I'm okay.

1434
02:24:04,769 --> 02:24:06,619
Good. You're gonna be
all right, okay?

1435
02:24:16,313 --> 02:24:19,181
<i>This thing emerged from
the Kryptonian crash site</i>

1436
02:24:19,183 --> 02:24:20,983
<i>just moments ago.</i>

1437
02:24:20,985 --> 02:24:22,985
<i>Thankfully though, the work day is over</i>

1438
02:24:22,987 --> 02:24:25,521
<i>in the downtown core.
It's nearly empty.</i>

1439
02:24:25,523 --> 02:24:29,258
<i>Now military aircraft.
Those are apache helicopters.</i>

1440
02:24:29,260 --> 02:24:31,761
<i>They have now just arrived.
The images that...</i>

1441
02:25:07,998 --> 02:25:11,200
<i>We've, uh... We just lost
connection with Metropolis 8 news.</i>

1442
02:25:11,202 --> 02:25:13,536
<i>Now, it's not clear what just happened.</i>

1443
02:25:17,140 --> 02:25:18,708
<i>What's happening there, Alfred?</i>

1444
02:25:20,545 --> 02:25:22,511
How best to describe it?

1445
02:25:22,513 --> 02:25:24,413
<i>Metropolis airspace
has been closed briefly.</i>

1446
02:25:24,415 --> 02:25:25,981
Excuse me?

1447
02:25:25,983 --> 02:25:26,682
<i>We kindly ask that you stay in your seats.</i>

1448
02:25:26,684 --> 02:25:28,050
Excuse me?

1449
02:25:28,052 --> 02:25:29,452
Miss Prince?

1450
02:25:43,900 --> 02:25:45,901
Sir. Look,
they've cleared the city.

1451
02:25:45,903 --> 02:25:47,570
Looks like he's taking it into space.

1452
02:25:47,572 --> 02:25:49,405
We can go straight to key red,
Mr. President.

1453
02:25:49,407 --> 02:25:51,040
Not yet. Are you crazy?

1454
02:25:51,042 --> 02:25:52,341
They're high enough that we can nuke 'em

1455
02:25:52,343 --> 02:25:53,709
with no casualties, sir.

1456
02:25:53,711 --> 02:25:56,645
One casualty, Mr. President.
Superman.

1457
02:25:59,217 --> 02:26:00,583
<i>God have mercy on us all.</i>

1458
02:26:06,923 --> 02:26:08,958
Key is hot.
Key is hot.

1459
02:26:08,960 --> 02:26:10,993
Red birds are armed to deploy, sir.

1460
02:26:12,262 --> 02:26:13,562
<i>Fire at will.</i>

1461
02:26:13,564 --> 02:26:15,598
Three, two, one...

1462
02:27:04,614 --> 02:27:05,915
<i>Oh, God.</i>

1463
02:27:28,138 --> 02:27:29,505
Projectile 1. Impact.

1464
02:27:29,507 --> 02:27:31,540
Stryker's island, east of Metropolis.

1465
02:27:31,542 --> 02:27:32,842
That's uninhabited.

1466
02:27:32,844 --> 02:27:34,376
Projectile 2...

1467
02:27:39,950 --> 02:27:42,151
No apparent reentry.

1468
02:27:42,153 --> 02:27:44,119
<i>Projectile 2?</i>

1469
02:27:44,121 --> 02:27:49,959
Superman, Mr. President.
Projectile 2 was Superman.

1470
02:27:49,961 --> 02:27:51,260
Sir.

1471
02:27:51,962 --> 02:27:53,095
It's moving.

1472
02:28:34,537 --> 02:28:36,238
<i>The shockwaves are getting stronger.</i>

1473
02:28:36,240 --> 02:28:39,408
Every time we hit it,
we make it more powerful.

1474
02:28:39,410 --> 02:28:42,077
We can't attack.

1475
02:28:42,079 --> 02:28:44,546
<i>What are you saying, Calvin?</i>

1476
02:28:44,548 --> 02:28:46,782
I'm saying it's unkillable.

1477
02:29:14,277 --> 02:29:16,612
Master Wayne, are you receiving me?

1478
02:29:16,614 --> 02:29:17,780
<i>Alfred.</i>

1479
02:29:17,782 --> 02:29:19,615
<i>It's Kryptonian.</i>

1480
02:29:19,617 --> 02:29:22,318
<i>Only kryptonite weapons can kill it.</i>

1481
02:29:22,320 --> 02:29:25,487
They might.
If you had any left.

1482
02:29:25,489 --> 02:29:28,958
<i>I got one round left.</i>

1483
02:29:28,960 --> 02:29:33,128
<i>The spear. Alfred, the spear.
It's pure kryptonite.</i>

1484
02:29:33,130 --> 02:29:34,897
<i>It's back in Gotham.</i>

1485
02:29:34,899 --> 02:29:37,766
<i>If I can penetrate the skin,
the spear will kill it.</i>

1486
02:29:37,768 --> 02:29:39,435
It would in theory.

1487
02:29:39,437 --> 02:29:41,937
<i>I've gotta get it to chase me
back to the city.</i>

1488
02:29:41,939 --> 02:29:43,672
<i>Back to the kryptonite.</i>

1489
02:30:44,334 --> 02:30:45,934
<i>Oh, shit.</i>

1490
02:31:35,352 --> 02:31:37,419
Why did you bring him back to the city?

1491
02:31:37,421 --> 02:31:38,921
<i>The port is abandoned.</i>

1492
02:31:38,923 --> 02:31:40,873
<i>There's a weapon here that can kill it.</i>

1493
02:31:53,369 --> 02:31:54,636
Did you find the spear?

1494
02:31:55,605 --> 02:31:57,372
<i>I've been a little busy.</i>

1495
02:31:57,374 --> 02:32:00,676
This thing, this creature,
seems to feed on energy.

1496
02:32:02,745 --> 02:32:05,647
This thing is from another world.

1497
02:32:06,316 --> 02:32:07,649
My world.

1498
02:32:07,651 --> 02:32:10,319
I've killed things
from other worlds before.

1499
02:32:11,955 --> 02:32:13,155
Is she with you?

1500
02:32:14,124 --> 02:32:16,024
<i>I thought she was with you.</i>

1501
02:35:54,477 --> 02:35:56,011
Clark!

1502
02:35:56,013 --> 02:35:57,379
Clark!

1503
02:36:04,854 --> 02:36:05,921
Clark!

1504
02:36:16,400 --> 02:36:18,300
Clark!

1505
02:36:18,302 --> 02:36:19,935
Clark! Are you all right?

1506
02:36:57,740 --> 02:36:59,474
I love you.

1507
02:37:03,079 --> 02:37:06,515
No. No, Clark, you can't.

1508
02:37:08,251 --> 02:37:10,185
This is my world.

1509
02:37:10,187 --> 02:37:11,653
No, Clark, don't.

1510
02:37:15,258 --> 02:37:17,626
You are my world.

1511
02:37:17,628 --> 02:37:18,760
No.

1512
02:37:21,931 --> 02:37:23,665
Please. Clark!

1513
02:44:29,625 --> 02:44:30,692
Hi.

1514
02:44:37,700 --> 02:44:40,435
Clark had this sent here,
so he could surprise you.

1515
02:47:07,516 --> 02:47:09,684
"The dead shall live.

1516
02:47:10,519 --> 02:47:13,755
"My slain shall rise again.

1517
02:47:16,725 --> 02:47:19,594
"Awake and sing, ye that dwell in dust.

1518
02:47:21,030 --> 02:47:24,365
"For thy dew is like the dew of morning.

1519
02:47:26,201 --> 02:47:31,139
"And the earth shall
give birth to her dead."

1520
02:47:38,547 --> 02:47:41,215
Ah, I need a ride back to the house.

1521
02:47:41,217 --> 02:47:43,918
I forgot my checkbook
to pay the funeral director.

1522
02:47:43,920 --> 02:47:46,054
They said it's all taken care of.

1523
02:47:46,056 --> 02:47:47,121
By whom?

1524
02:47:48,057 --> 02:47:49,791
Anonymous donor.

1525
02:48:33,602 --> 02:48:37,772
All those circuses back east
burying an empty box.

1526
02:48:37,774 --> 02:48:39,841
They don't know how to honor him,

1527
02:48:40,876 --> 02:48:42,677
except as a soldier.

1528
02:48:44,446 --> 02:48:47,782
I've failed him in life.

1529
02:48:49,251 --> 02:48:53,054
I won't fail him in death.

1530
02:48:53,056 --> 02:48:55,723
Help me find the others like you.

1531
02:48:55,725 --> 02:48:57,658
Perhaps they don't want to be found.

1532
02:48:58,594 --> 02:49:01,395
They will.
And they'll fight.

1533
02:49:02,598 --> 02:49:04,565
We have to stand together.

1534
02:49:12,307 --> 02:49:15,543
100 years ago, I walked away from mankind.

1535
02:49:17,613 --> 02:49:19,580
From a century of horrors.

1536
02:49:23,152 --> 02:49:26,854
Man made a world where standing
together is impossible.

1537
02:49:29,925 --> 02:49:31,859
Men are still good.

1538
02:49:34,329 --> 02:49:37,231
<i>We fight. We kill.</i>

1539
02:49:38,433 --> 02:49:40,835
<i>We betray one another.</i>

1540
02:49:42,704 --> 02:49:44,772
<i>But we can rebuild.</i>

1541
02:49:46,008 --> 02:49:47,875
<i>We can do better.</i>

1542
02:49:49,144 --> 02:49:51,179
<i>We will.</i>

1543
02:49:51,181 --> 02:49:52,380
<i>We have to.</i>

1544
02:50:15,470 --> 02:50:17,038
The others like me.

1545
02:50:17,040 --> 02:50:19,307
Why did you say they'll have to fight?

1546
02:50:24,713 --> 02:50:26,948
Just a feeling.

1547
02:50:38,160 --> 02:50:40,761
Prisoner A-C-23-19-40.

1548
02:50:40,763 --> 02:50:43,513
The Warden wants to speak to you,
so stand to your feet.

1549
02:50:45,100 --> 02:50:47,001
I'm gonna say this one more time.

1550
02:50:47,003 --> 02:50:49,804
The Warden wants to speak to you,
so stand to your feet.

1551
02:50:57,679 --> 02:50:59,580
Turn around and face the wall.

1552
02:51:01,617 --> 02:51:04,018
Place your forehead against the wall.

1553
02:51:04,020 --> 02:51:05,920
Put your hands behind your back,

1554
02:51:05,922 --> 02:51:07,989
so that I can come in and restrain you.

1555
02:51:36,285 --> 02:51:39,220
<i>Whatever you do, wherever you go,</i>

1556
02:51:39,222 --> 02:51:41,322
<i>I'll be watching you.</i>

1557
02:51:41,957 --> 02:51:43,357
Oh...

1558
02:51:44,793 --> 02:51:46,360
Look at us.

1559
02:51:47,462 --> 02:51:49,764
This is how it all caves in.

1560
02:51:49,766 --> 02:51:55,169
Civilization on the Wayne
manor's out the window.

1561
02:51:55,171 --> 02:51:56,737
Mmm?

1562
02:51:59,242 --> 02:52:02,143
But who would believe me?
I...

1563
02:52:02,145 --> 02:52:04,578
I'm insane.

1564
02:52:05,847 --> 02:52:08,015
I'm not even fit to stand trial.

1565
02:52:08,017 --> 02:52:09,950
That's right.

1566
02:52:09,952 --> 02:52:13,788
We have hospitals that treat the
mentally ill with compassion.

1567
02:52:15,091 --> 02:52:17,091
But that's not where you're going.

1568
02:52:17,093 --> 02:52:20,594
I arranged for you to get transferred
to Arkham Asylum in Gotham.

1569
02:52:21,997 --> 02:52:24,532
I still have some friends there.

1570
02:52:24,534 --> 02:52:26,167
They're expecting you.

1571
02:52:30,672 --> 02:52:34,909
But the bell's already been rung.

1572
02:52:37,379 --> 02:52:38,846
And they've heard it.

1573
02:52:40,682 --> 02:52:42,450
Out in the dark.

1574
02:52:42,452 --> 02:52:45,119
Among the stars. Hmm.

1575
02:52:48,190 --> 02:52:51,759
Ding dong, the God is dead.

1576
02:53:01,136 --> 02:53:03,938
But a bell cannot be unrung!

1577
02:53:05,240 --> 02:53:08,776
He's hungry.
He's found us.

1578
